Irene Losses for Cat Bond Index Reach $2.82 Billion, RMS Says

-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 
2011-09-20T15:26:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/irene-losses-for-cat-bond-index-reach-2-82-billion-rms-says.html
Irene, the first hurricane to
strike the U.S. since 2008, caused $2.82 billion of losses
according to an index used by catastrophe bond investors, Risk
Management Solutions Inc. said.  The total cost to insurers will be between $2 billion and
$4.5 billion in the U.S., the Newark, California-based company
said today in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
 nbuhayar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  